🏥 Lightweight Blockchain-Based Framework for Secure Healthcare IoT Data Sharing

## 📌 Overview

This project presents a **secure and efficient healthcare data sharing system** using a combination of **lightweight encryption, dynamic key management, and blockchain-based integrity verification**.

Unlike traditional systems that rely on computationally expensive encryption techniques, this framework focuses on **scalability, performance, and real-time usability** in Healthcare IoT environments.

---

## 🎯 Key Features

* 🔐 **Dynamic Key Derivation** (No key storage required)
* ⚡ **AES-GCM Encryption** for fast and secure data protection
* ⛓️ **Blockchain Integration** for tamper-proof verification
* 📊 **Hash-Based Integrity Checking (SHA-256)**
* 📁 **Off-chain Storage** for scalable data management
* 👤 **Patient-Centric Data Organization**
* 🚀 **High Performance & Low Computational Overhead**

---

## 🧠 System Architecture

```text
Data Collection (FHIR JSON)
        ↓
Patient-wise Grouping
        ↓
Dynamic Key Derivation
        ↓
AES-GCM Encryption
        ↓
SHA-256 Hash Generation
        ↓
Blockchain Storage (Hash)
        ↓
Off-chain Storage (Encrypted Data)
        ↓
Data Retrieval & Verification
        ↓
Secure Decryption
```

